Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of fifteen (15) years.  That is seven (7) years initial confinement followed by eight (8) years extended supervision, consecutive to the sentence presently serving.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for the Substance Abuse Program but not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
The defendant has credit for 418 days.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) no contact with Tyler Higgins, the victim or any known drug dealers or users;
6) no possession of any weapons;
7) pay court costs of $518.00;
8) provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
